body:
@craig1583 It would be good for you to share the overall design with the community. 
I know both YARN and Mesos support node labels. That's why you expanded `EvaluatorRequest`? 
How do you support node labels in the stand-alone runtime? Do other resource managers such as Kubernetes support node labels as well?

Thank you for your reviews.
@markusweimer As @bgchun mentioned, I expanded `EvaluatorRequest` to provide an interface that supports both node labeling on YARN and node attributes on Mesos. I will share my overall design and plan on [REEF-1758](https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/REEF-1758). So far, Iâ€™ve considered only YARN and Mesos, but I think supporting node labels in stand-alone runtime would be needed as well. I will have a think about that.

This [document](https://kubernetes.io/docs/concepts/configuration/assign-pod-node/#step-one-attach-label-to-the-node
) says Kubernetes also supports node labeling. I will examine whether other resource managers support it.

@motus 
I tried to create an unit test for this, but currently `_uriPrefix` in `HadoopFileSystem` is set to be `private`. The key to this test is to have an uppercase `_uriPrefix` to text if it is cast into lowercase. I can make `GetUriPrefix()` public for testing, but I don't think it is a good practice.

Do you have a better approach? Thanks!

OK - one failure in VS2013 which looks like an intermittent test. Passes in VS2015 and VS2017. 

@markusweimer 
@jwang98052 
@motus 

Can one of you take a final look? Thank you!
